# Project Rule: MIT-BIH Arrhythmia Multi-Class Classification

This project uses the MIT-BIH Arrhythmia Dataset to implement a multi-class arrhythmia classification pipeline.

- Dataset: MIT-BIH Arrhythmia Dataset
- Main goal: Classify multiple arrhythmia types from ECG signals
- Data preprocessing, augmentation, and train/val/test splitting are required
- Models: Experiment with various deep learning models (CNN, RNN, Transformer, etc.)
- Evaluation metrics: Use metrics suitable for multi-class classification (Accuracy, F1-score, Confusion Matrix, etc.)
- Ensure reproducibility by fixing random seeds and recording experiment environments
- Code structure should be modular: data loading, preprocessing, model definition, training, evaluation, and result visualization

- Reference: [MIT-BIH Arrhythmia Dataset official documentation](mdc:https://physionet.org/content/mitdb/1.0.0/)